ðŸ“Œ SQL SUBQUERY (NOTES + TYPES + EXAMPLES)
=====================================================================

A SUBQUERY is a **query inside another query**.
It is also called **nested query**.

Used to:
âœ” Filter data  
âœ” Compare values  
âœ” Perform complex queries easily  

====================================================================
# TYPES OF SUBQUERIES
====================================================================

âœ” Single-row Subquery  
âœ” Multiple-row Subquery  
âœ” Correlated Subquery  

====================================================================
# 1ï¸âƒ£ SINGLE-ROW SUBQUERY
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ SINGLE-ROW SUBQUERY
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Returns **only ONE value**.

USED WITH OPERATORS:
=   >   <   >=   <=

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select name, population
from world
where population >
(
  select population
  from world
  where name = 'Germany'
);

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 2ï¸âƒ£ MULTIPLE-ROW SUBQUERY
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ MULTIPLE-ROW SUBQUERY
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Returns **MORE THAN ONE value**.

USED WITH OPERATORS:
IN, ANY, ALL

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ IN
------------------------------------------------------------
EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select name
from world
where continent in
(
  select continent
  from world
  where name = 'India'
);

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ ANY
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Condition true if **any one** value matches.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select name, population
from world
where population > ANY
(
  select population
  from world
  where continent = 'Europe'
);

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ ALL
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Condition true if value matches **all** values.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select name, population
from world
where population > ALL
(
  select population
  from world
  where continent = 'Europe'
);

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 3ï¸âƒ£ CORRELATED SUBQUERY
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ CORRELATED SUBQUERY
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Subquery that **depends on outer query**.
Runs **once for each row**.

KEY POINT:
âœ” Uses outer query column  
âœ” Slower but powerful  

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select name, continent, population
from world w1
where population >
(
  select avg(population)
  from world w2
  where w1.continent = w2.continent
);

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
COMPARISON SUMMARY
====================================================================

| Type            | Returns        | Operators Used      |
|-----------------|---------------|---------------------|
| Single-row      | One value     | =, >, <             |
| Multiple-row    | Many values   | IN, ANY, ALL        |
| Correlated      | Per row value | Depends on outer    |

====================================================================
INTERVIEW ONE-LINERS
====================================================================

âœ” Subquery â†’ query inside another query  
âœ” Single-row â†’ returns one value  
âœ” Multiple-row â†’ returns many values  
âœ” Correlated â†’ runs per row  

âœ” Correlated subquery is **slower** than normal subquery  

====================================================================
SUMMARY
====================================================================

âœ” Subqueries simplify complex logic  
âœ” Used in WHERE, HAVING, SELECT  
âœ” Correlated subquery depends on outer query  

